text:
The commissioner of health shall implement a climate resiliency program to:
(1) increase awareness of climate change;
(2) track the public health impacts of climate change and extreme weather events;
(3) provide technical assistance and tools that support climate resiliency to local public health departments, Tribal health departments, soil and water conservation districts, and other local governmental and nongovernmental organizations; and
(4) coordinate with the commissioners of the Pollution Control Agency, natural resources, and agriculture and other state agencies in climate resiliency related planning and implementation.
